Okay, so where are some of these poems? As the former wife of a VN vet, and one who, like everyone else, lost friends there, I have some poems of my own, and am ready to post one or two, also. But I'd like to chat with Bob after seeing his work, because when I finished my MA, I wrote a novel which featured--you guessed it--a (somewhat damaged, emotionally) VN vet; it was a &quot;contemporary love story&quot; that didn't really have much love in it, only people's sad attempts to connect without really having dealt with the old wounds. The women left behind have plenty of baggage, too, which was also part of the point of my book. So Bob, good luck with your thesis, and if I ever do find your actual poems in this site, I'll be glad to give my feedback, and post some of my own. P. S. I've been teaching college English for the last several years, and no matter which class I'm teaching, I'm very big on reminding the war-less generation on the horrors of it all and the absolute necessity of never engaging again...for whatever that's worth.
